way play and [[Disney]] motion picture ''[[The Happiest Millionaire]]'' ******* [[Anthony Joseph Drexel Biddle, Jr.]] (1897–1961), U.S. ambassador to seven different countries, married [[Mary Duke Biddle|Mary Duke]] (1887–1960), the sister of Angier Buchanan Duke ******** [[Mary Duke Biddle Trent Semans|Mary Duke Biddle]] (1920–2012), heiress and philanthropist ******** Nicholas Duke Biddle (1921-2004) ******* Cordelia Drexel Biddle (1898–1984), married [[Angier Buchanan Duke]] (1884–1923), the brother of Mary Duke ******** [[Angier Biddle Duke]] (1915–1995), U.S. Ambassador to [[El Salvador]] 1952–1953, U.S. Ambassador to [[Spain]] 1965–1968, U.S. Ambassador to [[Morocco]] 1979–1981, member of the [[Council on Foreign Relations]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://politicalgraveyard.com/bio/duke.html#RJW0Z6JI0|title=The Political Graveyard: Index to Politicians: Duke|last=Kestenbaum|first=Lawrence|website=politicalgraveyard.com|access-date=2016-04-09}}</ref> ******** {{Tree list/final branch}}Anthony Drexel Duke (1918-2014) ******* {{Tree list/final branch}}Livingston Ludlow Biddle (1899–1981) married Kate Raboteau Page (1903–?), daughter of [[Robert N. Page]] ******** {{Tree list/final branch}}Livingston Ludlow Biddle (1926–2009) married Elizabeth "Betsy" Elwell Collin in 1953<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bocabeacon.com/?p=1980 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-10-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101224111456/http://www.bocabeacon.com/?p=1980 |archivedate=2010-12-24 |df= }}</ref><ref name="BiddlePitt">{{cite news|title=Biddle|url=https://www.pittsburghlive.com/x/pittsburghtrib/news/pittsburgh/s_623092.html|accessdate=27 November 2017|work=Pittsburgh Live}}{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>http://www.pittsburghlive.com/x/pittsburghtrib/news/pittsburgh/s_623092.html{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> ****** Livingston Ludlow Biddle (1877–1959), 