[[image:embassy theater cumberland.jpg|thumb]] The '''Embassy Theatre''' is a performance theater located in the downtown mall of [[Cumberland, Maryland]] at 49 Baltimore St. The theater mounts live performances of classic theatre fare such as [[Kurt Weill]]'s ''[[Threepenny Opera]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.alleganyartscouncil.org/event.php?eventid=501|title = The Threepenny Opera|date = |accessdate = 13 November 2014|website = The Allegany Arts Council|publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> and [[Kander and Ebb]]'s ''[[Cabaret (musical)|Cabaret]],'' as well as lesser-known work such as "The Mystery of Irma Vep" and "The Lady In Question," original works and local historical plays. Other entertainment presented at the theatre includes movies and musical concerts. Originally opened as a movie theater in 1931, it then became a curtain and drapery store, and finally was remodeled to a live performance theater and allied arts venue. Until December 2014, the theatre was operated as the New Embassy Theatre. Recently remodeled, it now operates as the Embassy Theatre. <ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.times-news.com/opinion/article_9e0433e8-79e4-5129-ae1e-5b70565fda7e.html?mode=jqm|title = Friends of Film|date = |accessdate = 13 November 2014|website = Cumberland Times News|publisher = Cumberland Times News|last = |first = }}</ref>
