{{Infobox Person
| name            = Frances Yung Ming Fong
| birth_date      = 1972 
| occupation      = Director of Hong Kong Eastern Harbour Tunnel Company
}}

'''Frances Yung Ming Fong''' (born 1972 with family roots in [[Wuxi]], [[Jiangsu]]) was the [[finance director|director]] of Group [[Finance]] Department of [[CITIC Pacific]]. She is the [[deputy chairman]] of CITIC Pacific Communications Limited and the director of Hong Kong [[Eastern Harbour Tunnel]] Company. She is the [[daughter]] of [[Larry Yung Chi Kin]], the former chairman of CITIC Pacific.<ref>[http://www.citicpacific.com/eng/about/mgnt_sm4.html Frances Yung Ming Fong]</ref>

== 2008 CITIC Pacific foreign exchange losses ==
{{main|CITIC Pacific#2008 foreign exchange losses controversy}}

In October 2008, Yung and other two senior executives were involved in an unauthorized [[foreign exchange market|foreign exchange]] deals in [[CITIC Pacific]], which caused a [[HK$]]15.5 billion [[Income statement|loss]] in the company. Then she was removed from the finance department and [[Demotion|demoted]] with a [[salary]] cut, confirmed by [[Henry Fan]], the CITIC Pacific's [[managing director]].<ref>[http://www.thestandard.com.hk/news_detail.asp?pp_cat=30&art_id=73228&sid=21102411&con_type=3 How much did daddy's girl know?]</ref>

