The '''Gay Financial Network''' was created by [[Walter Schubert]]<ref>{{cite web | last = Staff writer | title = Walter Schubert: founder and chairman Gay Financial Network | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090521103210/http://www.nglcc.org/about/board/schubert | archive-date = 21 May 2009 | url = http://www.nglcc.org/about/board/schubert | website = nglcc.org | publisher = [[National Gay & Lesbian Chamber of Commerce]] | access-date = 31 January 2016 }}</ref> in April 1998.<ref name="Changing Corporate America">{{citation | last = Raeburn | first = Nicole C. | contribution = Winds of change outside corporate walls: external factors influence gay-inclusive poliicies | editor-last = Raeburn | editor-first = Nicole C. | title = Changing corporate America from inside out: lesbian and gay workplace rights | pages = 140–141 | publisher = [[University of Minnesota Press]] | location = Minneapolis | year = 2004 | isbn = 9780816639984 | ref = harv | postscript = .}} [https://books.google.com/books?id=P2rdnDOqAagC&pg=PA140&dq=%22Gay+Financial+Network%22#PPA141,M1 Preview.]</ref> It aims to single out businesses which practice discrimination on the basis of sexual orientation.<ref>{{cite news | last = Spurdon | first = Stephen | title = Money: As sound as a pink pound | url = https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/money-as-sound-as-a-pink-pound-1093955.html | work = [[The Independent]] | publisher = Independent Print Ltd. | date = 16 May 1999 | access-date = 31 January 2016 }}</ref> It was the first gay-specific company to be advertised in ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'', on February 18, 2000<ref name="Changing Corporate America"/> and has been seen as an example of the merging of gay activism with gay marketing.<ref>{{citation | last = Danuta Walters | first = Suzanna | author-link = Suzanna Danuta Walters | contribution = If it's pink we'll sell it: gay entrepreneurship | editor-last = Danuta Walters | editor-first = Suzanna | editor-link = Suzanna Danuta Walters | title = All the rage: the story of gay visibility in America | page = 282 | publisher = [[Chicago University Press]] | location = Chicago | year = 2001 | isbn = 9780226872315 | ref = harv | postscript = .}} [https://books.google.com/books?id=2pSH73isp94C&pg=PA282&dq=%22Gay+Financial+Network%22 Preview.]</ref>
